mmunalnik Pinsk]].\n*<sup>'''3, 4'''</sup> 3 points deducted for unpaid transfer.\n\n==Belshina in European Cups==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Season\n! Competition\n! Round\n!\n!width=130| Club\n! 1st Leg\n! 2nd Leg\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[1997\u201398 UEFA Cup Winners' Cup|1997\u201398]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[UEFA Cup Winners' Cup]]\n|QR\n|{{flagicon|Estonia}}\n|[[JK Tallinna Sadam|Sadam Tallinn]]\n|1\u20131 (A)\n|4\u20131 (H)\n|-\n|1R\n|{{flagicon|Russia}}\n|[[FC Lokomotiv Moscow|Lokomotiv Moscow]]\n|1\u20132 (H)\n|0\u20133 (A)\n|-\n|[[1998\u201399 UEFA Cup|1998\u201399]]\n|[[UEFA Cup]]\n|1Q\n|{{flagicon|Bulgaria}}\n|[[PFC CSKA Sofia|CSKA Sofia]]\n|0\u20130 (A)\n|1\u20133 (H)\n|-\n|[[1999\u20132000 UEFA Cup|1999\u20132000]]\n|[[UEFA Cup]]\n|QR\n|{{flagicon|Cyprus}}\n|[[AC Omonia|Omonia]]\n|1\u20135 (H)\n|0\u20133 (A)\n|-\n|[[2001\u201302 UEFA Cup|2001\u201302]]\n|[[UEFA Cup]]\n|QR\n|{{flagicon|Slovakia}}\n|[[MFK Ru\u017eomberok|Ru\u017eomberok]]\n|1\u20133 (A)\n|0\u20130 (H)\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[2002\u201303 UEFA Champions League|2002\u201303]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[UEFA Champions League]]\n|1Q\n|{{flagicon|Northern Ireland}}\n|[[Portadown F.C.|Portadown]]\n|0\u20130 (A)\n|3\u20132 (H)\n|-\n|2Q\n|{{flagicon|Israel}}\n|[[Maccabi Haifa F.C.|Maccabi Haifa]]\n|0\u20134 (A)\n|0\u20131 (H)\n|}\n\n==Managers==\n*{{flagicon|Belarus}} [[Liudas Rumbutis]] (July 1, 1998&nbsp;\u2013 Dec 31, 1999), (Jan 1, 2003&nbsp;\u2013 Dec 31, 2003)\n*{{flagicon|Belarus}} [[Vladimir Gevorkyan]] (Jan 1, 2003&nbsp;\u2013 Jan 13, 2004)\n*{{flagicon|Belarus}} [[Oleg Volokh]] ''(interim)'' (May 14, 2004&nbsp;\u2013 May 27, 2004)\n*{{flagicon|Belarus}} [[Sergei Borovsky]] (Sept 3, 2004&nbsp;\u2013 Dec 31, 2004)\n*{{flagicon|Belarus}} [[Oleg Volokh]] (Jan 1, 2006&nbsp;\u2013 May 11, 2006)\n*{{flagicon|Belarus}} [[Mikhail Markhel]] (May 16, 2006&nbsp;\u2013 Dec 31, 2006)\n*{{flagicon|Belarus}} [[Aleksandr Sednev]] (Jan 1, 2009&nbsp;\u2013 Nov 30, 2011)\n*{{flagicon|Belarus}} [[Sergey Yaromko]] (Jan 1, 2012&nbsp;\u2013 July 21, 2012)\n*{{flagicon|Ukraine}} [[Vitaliy Pavlov (footballer, born 1965)|Vitaliy Pavlov]] ''(caretaker)'' (July 21, 2012&nbsp;\u2013 July 23, 2012)\n*{{flagicon|Belarus}} [[Aleksandr Sednev]] (July 23, 2012&nbsp;\u2013 December 31, 2015)\n*{{flagicon|Ukraine}} [[Vitaliy Pavlov (footballer, born 1965)|Vitaliy Pavlov]] (January 1, 2016&nbsp;\u2013 )\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.fcbelshina.by/ Official website]\n\n{{Belarusian Premier League teamlist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Belshina Bobruislk}}\n[[Category:Football clubs in Belarus]]\n[[Category:Association football clubs established in 1976]]\n[[Category:Babruysk]]\n[[Category:1976 establishments in Belarus]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football club\n| clubname = FC Belshina Bobruisk\n| image    = FC Belshyna Babruisk.png\n| fullname = Football Club Belshina\n| nickname = \n| founded  = 1976\n| ground   = [[Spartak Stadium (Bobruisk)|Spartak Stadium]], [[Bobruisk]]\n| capacity = 3,700\n| chairman = Mikhail Bondarenko\n| manager  = [[Eduard Gradoboyev]]\n| league   = [[Belarusian Premier League]]\n| season   = [[2019 Belarusian First League|2019]]\n| position = [[Belarusian First League]], 1st (promoted)\n| website  = http://www.fcbelshina.by\n| pattern_la1 = |pattern_b1 = _hb1819h |pattern_ra1 = |pattern_sh1 = |pattern_so1 = \n| leftarm1 = FF0000 |body1 = FF0000 |rightarm1 = FF0000 |shorts1 = FFFFFF |socks1 = FF0000\n| pattern_la2 =_redbull1718h |pattern_b2 = _redbull1718h |pattern_ra2 =_redbull1718h |pattern_sh2 = _whitesides |pattern_so2 = \n| leftarm2 = DDDDDD |body2 = DDDDDD |rightarm2 = DDDDDD |shorts2 = FFFFFF |socks2 = FFFFFF\n}}\n\n'''FC Belshina Bobruisk''' ({{lang-be|\u0424\u041a \"\u0411\u0435\u043b\u0448\u044b\u043d\u0430 \u0411\u0430\u0431\u0440\u0443\u0439\u0441\u043a\"}}, ''FK Belshyna Babruisk'') is a [[Belarus]]ian [[association football|football]] club based in [[Bobruisk]]. The team has won one [[Belarusian Premier League]] title, as well as 3 [[Belarusian Cup]] titles, in post-Soviet Belarus.\n\n==History of the club and football in Bobruisk==\nThe city of Bobruisk was represented by its football team as early as 1920s, when in 1926 a collective football team of Bobruisk city won the Belarusian football championship. Winning the 1926, Bobruisk football team became the first from a provincial city that won the republican competitions. Until 1958 it was the only achievement of the Bobruisk football. In 1958 ''Spartak Bobruisk'' became a champion of Belarus donating the second title to the Bobruisk city football.\n\nIn 1972 and 1973 ''Stroitel Bobruisk'' also won a title of the champion of Belarus.\n\nThe current club was founded in 1976 as '''Shinnik Bobruisk'''. Since the inception the team was attached to and later sponsored by local tire manufacturing company [[Belshina]]. The club spent most of Soviet-era seasons in [[Belarusian SSR]] league (with a couple of seasons in [[Mogilev Oblast]] league). Shinnik won the league title twice (in 1978 and 1987) and also won Belarusian SSR Cup in 1979.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fcbelshina.by/istoriya/kratkiy-ocherk-razvitiya-futbola-v-bobruyske.php|title=\u041a\u0440\u0430\u0442\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043e\u0447\u0435\u0440\u043a \u0440\u0430\u0437\u0432\u0438\u0442\u0438\u044f \u0444\u0443\u0442\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0430 \u0432 \u0411\u043e\u0431\u0440\u0443\u0439\u0441\u043a\u0435|author=|date=|work=fcbelshina.by|accessdate=8 February 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn 1992 Shinnik joined [[Belarusian First League]] and in 1994 they were promoted to [[Belarusian Premier League|Premier League]]. In 1996, they were renamed to '''Belshina Bobruisk'''. Club's most successful seasons came in late 90s and early 2000s. Belshina won the champions title in 2001, finished as runners-up in 1997 and won [[Belarusian Cup]] three times (1997, 1999, 2001).\n\n===Name changes===\n*1976: Founded as Shinnik Bobruisk\n*1996: Renamed to Belshina Bobruisk\n\n==Honours==\n* '''[[Belarusian Premier League]]'''\n** ''Winners (1):'' [[2001 Belarusian Premier League|2001]]\n** ''Runners-up (1):'' [[1997 Belarusian Premier League|1997]]\n** ''3rd place (2):'' [[1996 Belarusian Premier League|1996]], [[1998 Belarusian Premier League|1998]]\n* '''[[Belarusian Cup]]'''\n** ''Winners (3):'' [[1996\u201397 Belarusian Cup|1997]], [[1998\u201399 Belarusian Cup|1999]], [[2000\u201301 Belarusian Cup|2001]]\n\n==Current squad==\n''As of April 2020'' <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fcbelshina.by/komanda/osnovnoy-sostav/|title=\u041e\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0432\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432|website=www.fcbelshina.by}}</ref>\n\n{{Fs start}}\n{{Fs player|no=1|name=[[Aleksandr Svirskiy]]|nat=BLR|pos=GK}}\n{{Fs player|no=4|name=[[Vladislav Solanovich]]|nat=BLR|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=5|name=[[Konstantin Kuchinskiy]]|nat=BLR|pos=DF}}\n{{Fs player|no=6|name=[[German Barkovskiy]]|nat=BLR|pos=FW}}\n{{Fs player|no=7|name=[[Andrei Bezhonov]]|nat=RUS|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=8|name=[[Syarhey Hlyabko]]|nat=BLR|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=9|name=[[Leonid Kovel]]|nat=BLR|pos=FW}}\n{{Fs player|no=10|name=[[Pavel Bordukov]]|nat=BLR|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=11|name=[[Yevgeni Kirisov]]|nat=RUS|pos=DF}}\n{{Fs player|no=13|name=[[Aleksey Kharitonovich]]|nat=BLR|pos=GK}}\n{{Fs player|no=15|name=[[Danila Nechayev]]|nat=BLR|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=17|name=[[Yevgeni Skoblikov]]|nat=RUS|pos=FW}}\n{{Fs player|no=18|name=[[Roman Salimov]]|nat=RUS|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs mid}}\n{{Fs player|no=19|name=[[Mykhaylo Pysko]]|nat=UKR|pos=DF}}\n{{Fs player|no=21|name=[[Anton Novik]]|nat=BLR|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=22|name=[[Ilya Boltrushevich]]|nat=BLR|pos=DF}}\n{{Fs player|no=23|name=[[Samuel Odeyobo]]|nat=NGA|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=24|name=[[Sergey Turanok]]|nat=BLR|pos=GK}}\n{{Fs player|no=25|name=[[Mikhail Bashilov]]|nat=RUS|pos=DF}}\n{{Fs player|no=29|name=[[Dzmitry Rekish]]|nat=BLR|pos=MF}}\n{{Fs player|no=32|name=[[Vladislav Yasyukevich]]|nat=BLR|pos=DF}}\n{{Fs player|no=69|name=[[Nikita Rochev]